-- Eaton Breaks World Record in Decathlon at U.S. Olympic Trials
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-06-24T01:18:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-24/eaton-breaks-world-record-in-decathlon-at-u-s-olympic-trials.html
Ashton Eaton set a world record in
the decathlon during the U.S. Olympic trials.  Eaton, 24, finished the two-day decathlon series of events
with 9,039 points, 13 points ahead of Roman Sebrle who has held
the record for the past 11 years.  The trials are being held at the University of  Oregon  in
Eugene, Oregon.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  